env PAGER=cat man timing_report_max_transition_check_using_nsigma_ slew
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_report_...ng_nsigma_slew(25.10)  timing_report_...ng_nsigma_slew(25.10)

Name
       timing_report_max_transition_check_using_nsigma_slew

Syntax
       timing_report_max_transition_check_using_nsigma_slew

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables the report_constraint command to use mean and sigma slew values
       for reporting transition values in DRV checks.

       When  set  to true, in the SOCV flow the report_constraint command uses
       the mean plus n-sigma slew values for DRV checks.

       When set to false, the report_constraint command will report  only  the
       mean slews.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

